England and Italy are tied 0-0 at
the start of the second half in their quarterfinal at soccerâ€™s
European Championship.  The winner of the match at the Olympic Stadium in Kiev,
Ukraine will play record three-time champion Germany in the
semifinals.  England, which last reached the semifinals in 1996, is
looking to win the tournament for a first time. Italy is the
1968 champion.  England named an unchanged team, with  Wayne Rooney  again
partnering Manchester United teammate  Danny Welbeck  in attack.
Italy coach Cesare Prandelli recalled striker Mario Balotelli to
his starting lineup, while Riccardo Montolivo and Leonardo
Bonucci came in for the injured Giorgio Chiellini and Thiago
Motta.  The other semifinal will be between defending champion
Spain and Portugal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
